# Code Refactoring

Skill for refactoring BlitzBasic code including renaming, extracting functions, updating type fields, and improving code structure.

## When to Use

Use this skill when:
- Renaming variables or functions across files
- Extracting duplicate code into functions
- Updating Type field definitions
- Improving code structure
- Adding consistent error handling
- Standardizing code patterns

## Rename Refactoring

### Rename Function

```blitzbasic
; Rename a function across all files
; Run: RenameFunction "OldName" "NewName"

Function RenameFunction%(oldName$, newName$)
    ; Find all occurrences
    files$ = FindFiles("*.bb")

    ForEach file$ in files$
        content$ = ReadFile(file$)

        ; Replace function definition
        content$ = Replace(content$, "Function " + oldName$, "Function " + newName$)

        ; Replace function calls
        content$ = Replace(content$, oldName$ + "(", newName$ + "(")

        ; Write back
        WriteFile(file$, content$)
    Next

    Print "Renamed " + oldName$ + " to " + newName$ + " in " + CountFiles(files$) + " files"
End Function

; Example usage
; RenameFunction "OldUpdateNPC" "UpdateNPCv2"
; RenameFunction "CreateNPC_Old" "CreateNPC_New"
```

### Rename Variable

```blitzbasic
; Rename a variable across all files
; Run: RenameVariable "oldVar" "newVar" scope="global|local|all"

Function RenameVariable%(oldVar$, newVar$, scope$ = "all")
    files$ = FindFiles("*.bb")

    ForEach file$ in files$
        content$ = ReadFile(file$)

        ; Only process if not in strings
        lines$ = SplitLines(content$)

        ForEach line$ in lines$
            ; Skip if in string
            If Not InString(line$, """ + oldVar$ + """)

                ; Replace variable usage
                ; Be careful with partial matches
                pattern$ = "(^|[^a-zA-Z0-9_])" + oldVar$ + "([^a-zA-Z0-9_])"
                replacement$ = "$1" + newVar$ + "$2"

                line$ = RegexReplace(line$, pattern$, replacement$)
            End If
        Next

        WriteFile(file$, JoinLines(lines$))
    Next
End Function

; Example usage
; RenameVariable "oldHealth" "PlayerHealth"
; RenameVariable "tempNPC" "currentNPC" scope="local"
```

### Rename Type

```blitzbasic
; Rename a Type definition
; Run: RenameType "OldType" "NewType"

Function RenameType%(oldType$, newType$)
    files$ = FindFiles("*.bb")

    ForEach file$ in files$
        content$ = ReadFile(file$)

        ; Replace Type definition
        content$ = Replace(content$, "Type " + oldType$, "Type " + newType$)

        ; Replace variable declarations
        content$ = Replace(content$, oldType$ + ".", newType$ + ".")

        ; Replace New statements
        content$ = Replace(content$, "New " + oldType$, "New " + newType$)

        ; Replace Handle calls
        content$ = Replace(content$, "Handle(" + oldType$, "Handle(" + newType$)

        WriteFile(file$, content$)
    Next
End Function

; Example usage
; RenameType "NPC" "NPCs"
; RenameType "Item" "Items"
```

## Extract Function

### Extract Duplicate Code

```blitzbasic
; Extract duplicate code into a new function
; Run: ExtractFunction startLine endLine newFunctionName

Function ExtractFunction%(startLine%, endLine%, funcName$, targetFile$ = "")
    ; Read source file
    content$ = ReadFile(targetFile$)
    lines$ = SplitLines(content$)

    ; Extract code
    code$ = ""
    For i = startLine To endLine
        code$ = code$ + lines$[i] + Chr(10)
    Next

    ; Analyze parameters
    params$ = AnalyzeParameters(code$)

    ; Generate function
    newFunc$ = "Function " + funcName$ + "(" + params$ + ")" + Chr(10)
    newFunc$ = newFunc$ + IndentCode(code$, 4)
    newFunc$ = newFunc$ + "End Function" + Chr(10)

    ; Insert function before extraction point
    InsertLine(targetFile$, startLine - 1, newFunc$)

    ; Replace original code with call
    callLine$ = funcName$ + "(" + GenerateArguments(code$) + ")"
    ReplaceLines(targetFile$, startLine, endLine, callLine$)

    Print "Extracted " + funcName$ + " at line " + startLine
End Function

; Example: Extract movement code
; ExtractFunction 100 120 "CalculateMovementSpeed"
```

### Extract NPC Behavior

```blitzbasic
; Extract common NPC behavior into shared function
; Run: ExtractNPCBehavior behaviorName lines

Function ExtractNPCBehavior%(behaviorName$, startLine%, endLine%)
    ; This pattern is common across multiple NPCs
    code$ = ExtractCode(startLine, endLine)

    ; Create shared function
    func$ = "Function NPC_" + behaviorName$ + "%(npc.NPCs)" + Chr(10)
    func$ = func$ + IndentCode(code$, 4)
    func$ = func$ + "End Function" + Chr(10)

    ; Add to NPCs.bb
    AppendToFile("Sources/NPCs.bb", func$)

    ; Replace in all NPC update functions
    ReplaceInFiles("NPCs.bb", code$, "NPC_" + behaviorName$ + "(npc)")

    Print "Extracted NPC behavior: NPC_" + behaviorName$
End Function

; Example: Extract movement calculations
; ExtractNPCBehavior "MoveToTarget" 50 80
```

## Update Type Fields

### Add Field to Type

```blitzbasic
; Add a new field to a Type definition
; Run: AddField "TypeName" "FieldName" "FieldType"

Function AddFieldToType%(typeName$, fieldName$, fieldType$)
    ; Find the Type definition
    file$ = FindTypeDefinition(typeName$)
    If file$ = "" Then Return False

    content$ = ReadFile(file$)

    ; Find "End Type" and insert before it
    lines$ = SplitLines(content$)
    For i = 0 To CountLines(lines$) - 1
        If Trim(lines$[i]) = "End Type"
            ; Insert field before End Type
            lines$[i] = "    Field " + fieldName$ + fieldType$ + Chr(10) + "End Type"
            Exit
        End If
    Next

    WriteFile(file$, JoinLines(lines$))
    Print "Added field " + fieldName$ + " to Type " + typeName$
End Function

; Example usage
; AddFieldToType "NPCs" "AlertLevel#" ""
; AddFieldToType "Items" "Durability%" ""
; AddFieldToType "Player" "StaminaRegen#" ""
```

### Remove Field from Type

```blitzbasic
; Remove a field from a Type definition
; Run: RemoveField "TypeName" "FieldName"

Function RemoveFieldFromType%(typeName$, fieldName$)
    file$ = FindTypeDefinition(typeName$)
    If file$ = "" Then Return False

    content$ = ReadFile(file$)

    ; Remove field line
    pattern$ = "    Field " + fieldName$ + "[^" + Chr(10) + "]*"
    content$ = RegexReplace(content$, pattern$, "")

    WriteFile(file$, content$)
    Print "Removed field " + fieldName$ + " from Type " + typeName$
End Function
```

### Rename Field in Type

```blitzbasic
; Rename a field across all usage
; Run: RenameField "TypeName" "OldName" "NewName"

Function RenameFieldInType%(typeName$, oldName$, newName$)
    ; Update Type definition
    file$ = FindTypeDefinition(typeName$)
    content$ = ReadFile(file$)
    content$ = Replace(content$, "    Field " + oldName$, "    Field " + newName$)
    WriteFile(file$, content$)

    ; Update all usage
    RenameVariable(typeName$ + "\" + oldName$, typeName$ + "\" + newName$)
End Function
```

## Improve Structure

### Add Error Handling

```blitzbasic
; Wrap code with error handling
; Run: AddErrorHandling startLine endLine

Function AddErrorHandling%(startLine%, endLine%)
    file$ = GetCurrentFile()
    lines$ = ReadLines(file$)

    ; Add try-catch equivalent
    lines$[startLine] = "    ; === Error handling added ==="
    lines$[startLine] = "    errorOccurred = False"
    lines$[startLine] = "    errorMessage$ = """""

    ; Wrap code
    lines$[startLine] = "    If Not errorOccurred Then"
    lines$[startLine - 1] = "    errorOccurred = True"
    lines$[startLine - 1] = "    errorMessage$ = GetLastError()"
    lines$[startLine - 1] = "    CatchError:"

    WriteLines(file$, lines$)
    Print "Added error handling from line " + startLine + " to " + endLine
End Function
```

### Standardize Function

```blitzbasic
; Standardize function format
; Run: StandardizeFunction functionName

Function StandardizeFunction%(funcName$)
    ; Find function
    file$ = FindFunctionDefinition(funcName$)
    If file$ = "" Then Return False

    content$ = ReadFile(file$)

    ; Get function code
    funcCode$ = ExtractFunction(funcName$)

    ; Apply standard format
    standardized$ = "; ========================================" + Chr(10)
    standardized$ = standardized$ + "; " + funcName$ + Chr(10)
    standardized$ = standardized$ + "; ========================================" + Chr(10)
    standardized$ = standardized$ + StandardizeIndentation(funcCode$)

    ; Replace in file
    content$ = Replace(content$, funcCode$, standardized$)
    WriteFile(file$, content$)

    Print "Standardized function: " + funcName$
End Function
```

### Add Documentation

```blitzbasic
; Add documentation to function
; Run: DocumentFunction functionName description

Function DocumentFunction%(funcName$, description$)
    file$ = FindFunctionDefinition(funcName$)
    If file$ = "" Then Return False

    content$ = ReadFile(file$)

    ; Find function definition
    lines$ = SplitLines(content$)
    For i = 0 To CountLines(lines$) - 1
        If InString(lines$[i], "Function " + funcName$)
            ; Insert documentation before
            doc$ = "; " + description$ + Chr(10)
            doc$ = doc$ + "; Parameters:" + Chr(10)
            doc$ = doc$ = "; Returns:" + Chr(10)
            doc$ = doc$ = "; " + funcName$ + Chr(10)
            lines$[i] = doc$ + lines$[i]
            Exit
        End If
    Next

    WriteFile(file$, JoinLines(lines$))
    Print "Added documentation to " + funcName$
End Function
```

## Batch Refactoring

### Rename NPC Type

```blitzbasic
; Complete rename of NPC type across codebase
; Run: RenameNPCType "OldNPC" "NewNPC"

Function RenameNPCType%(oldType$, newType$)
    ; Rename Type
    RenameType(oldType$, newType$)

    ; Rename constants
    RenameVariable("NPC_" + Upper(oldType$), "NPC_" + Upper(newType$))

    ; Rename files
    If FileExists("Sources/NPCs/" + oldType$ + ".bb")
        RenameFile("Sources/NPCs/" + oldType$ + ".bb", "Sources/NPCs/" + newType$ + ".bb")
    End If

    ; Update NPCs.ini if exists
    If FileExists("Data/NPCs.ini")
        content$ = ReadFile("Data/NPCs.ini")
        content$ = Replace(content$, oldType$, newType$)
        WriteFile("Data/NPCs.ini", content$)
    End If

    Print "Renamed NPC type from " + oldType$ + " to " + newType$
End Function

; Example usage
; RenameNPCType "OldSCP173" "NewSCP173"
```

### Update All NPC Functions

```blitzbasic
; Update pattern across all NPC functions
; Run: UpdateAllNPCs pattern replacement

Function UpdateAllNPCs%(pattern$, replacement$)
    ; Update NPCs.bb
    file$ = "Sources/NPCs.bb"
    content$ = ReadFile(file$)
    content$ = Replace(content$, pattern$, replacement$)
    WriteFile(file$, content$)

    ; Update individual NPC files
    npcFiles$ = FindFiles("Sources/NPCs/*.bb")
    ForEach npcFile$ in npcFiles$
        content$ = ReadFile(npcFile$)
        content$ = Replace(content$, pattern$, replacement$)
        WriteFile(npcFile$, content$)
    Next

    Print "Updated pattern in " + CountFiles(npcFiles$) + " files"
End Function

; Example: Update all NPC speed to use new calculation
; UpdateAllNPCs "npc\Speed# = 4.0" "npc\Speed# = CalculateNPCSpeed(npc)"
```

## Quick Reference

| Command | Purpose |
|---------|---------|
| `RenameFunction "Old" "New"` | Rename function everywhere |
| `RenameVariable "old" "new"` | Rename variable everywhere |
| `RenameType "Old" "New"` | Rename Type everywhere |
| `ExtractFunction 100 120 "Name"` | Extract code to function |
| `AddField "Type" "Field" "Type"` | Add field to Type |
| `RemoveField "Type" "Field"` | Remove field from Type |
| `RenameField "Type" "Old" "New"` | Rename Type field |
| `AddErrorHandling 50 100` | Wrap code in error handling |
| `StandardizeFunction "Name"` | Standardize function format |
| `DocumentFunction "Name" "Desc"` | Add documentation |
| `RenameNPCType "Old" "New"` | Rename NPC type |
| `UpdateAllNPCs "pat" "rep"` | Update pattern in all NPCs |
